# Tech Stack — Afenda

## Monorepo Setup
- **Build System**: Turborepo + pnpm workspaces
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router, React Server Components)
- **UI**: shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS v4
- **Database**: Neon Postgres + Drizzle ORM
- **Auth**: Better Auth
- **Testing**: Vitest (unit) + Playwright (e2e)

## Project Structure
```
apps/
  web/          # Next.js app
  api/          # Backend API
  e2e/          # E2E tests
packages/
  db/           # Drizzle schemas
  contracts/    # Shared types
  core/         # Business logic
```

## Module Boundaries
- Web app imports from `packages/*` (never reverse)
- Each package has clear responsibility
- Check `architecture.*.md` before major changes

## Next.js MCP Workflow

**Before starting**:
1. Start dev server: `pnpm dev` or `pnpm --filter @afenda/web dev`
2. Call `init` tool (next-devtools-mcp) with `project_path: "apps/web"`
3. Use `nextjs_index` to inspect routes/components/errors

See `AGENTS.md` for full MCP conventions.

